            "text_TQ8dMx": {
              "type": "text",
              "settings": {
                "text": "<p>Before planting, we pay attention to how the land moves, where the sun falls, how the wind travels, where moisture lingers, and where the soil changes in depth, texture, and vitality. Rather than treating the estate as a uniform surface, we understand it as a living landscape of different conditions and possibilities.</p><p>This means working with the terrain rather than against it. We place species according to exposure, resilience, and ecological fit, allowing each area of the estate to guide what it can naturally support.</p><p>The result is a form of cultivation shaped by the land itself. More adaptive, more respectful and more resilient.</p>",
                "width": "fit-content",
                "max_width": "normal",
